<br>
Anyways, a few things. I believe football is as popular and widespread as it is simply because it is as old as it is. Also, the basic rules are fairly easy to grasp even if you are new to it, something not true to the same degree for american football for instance. <br>
<br>
However, I do not think its popularity has anything to do with the gear required to play it. It was mentioned that you can't really do well in american football if you can't fund the equipment, thus it is not played in poor countries. I dare say you *can* play it even then, since your neighbour is equally poor and thus you will be playing on equal terms still. All it truely takes to play american football is the ball, everything else is optional and can be improvised. Keep in mind that the global popularity for a sport is not determined by what you see on TV, with the big leagues playing in expensive gear. It is determined by what people, adults and children alike, prefer to play for fun. And at this level, most all sports are equal in terms of equipment needed: A ball and enough space to kick/throw it around. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=20820">Ulaian Moonleaf</A> - Warder <BR>
<A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=144917">Eandil Dayspring</A> - Templar <BR>
